  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b86\u0bb2\u0baf \u0b95\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bae\u0bcd ; \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8 - \u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb4\u0bcd  \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0ba3\u0ba9\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Nallur Temple Flag Hoisting; Ban on roundabout traffic - Jaffna Chief Minister Manivannan",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "As the annual celebration of the historic Nallur Kandaswamy Temple begins on the 2nd Tuesday with the hoisting of the flag, the Jaffna Municipal Council has given an explanation regarding its arrangements and procedures.",
        "A discussion regarding the Mahotsava arrangements was held at the Jaffna Municipal Council at 9.00 am on Tuesday morning.",
        "Jaffna Chief Minister Manivannan said that the Nallur Mahotsavam, which has been held on a limited scale for the last three years due to the Easter bomb blast and corona virus, will be held as usual, i.e. how the festival was held before the year 2018.",
        "After the discussion, Jaffna Chief Minister Manivannan said this while speaking to the media regarding Nallur temple celebrations.",
        "Further informed that, from the morning of August 1st, traffic will be prohibited on the Nallur temple roundabouts and will be opened only after the completion of Vairavar Shanti on August 29th.",
        "For any reason, no vehicles except the municipal council's water supply truck and sewage truck can enter the roadblock areas demarcated by red and white colored flags by the temple management around the outer road of the temple.",
        "Similarly, no commercial activities can be carried out within the road block areas demarcated by white colored flags. Drone cameras cannot be used to record video.",
        "All the ghouls who come to the temple to collect fines can only enter through the front of the temple, Parudhitura Road. Arrangements have been made for all the vehicles to exit through the Chettitheru road after the unloading of such incoming vehicles.",
        "When the road is closed, vehicles coming through Barudhitura Road can reach Jaffna through the road in front of the Jaffna Municipal Council. But during Redotsavam and Sappara festivals the concert can travel through Nallur Road only.",
        "Wearing face masks is not legalized. Even so, the devotees should wear face masks and follow the hygiene regulations as a result of the Corona warning. Every individual should take care of their health.",
        "In order to avoid incidents of theft, surveillance cameras will be installed by the Jaffna Municipal Council around the Nallur temple and measures will be taken.",
        "In this discussion, Jaffna City Chief Minister, City Commissioner, city officials, public health inspectors and other relevant departmental officials participated."
      ],
